                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.145,
                                "byte_start": 104603,
                                "byte_stop": 145250,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion this morning in case 07-330, Greenlaw versus United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.145,
                        "stop": 258.221,
                        "byte_start": 145250,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.145,
                                "stop": 22.172,
                                "byte_start": 145250,
                                "byte_stop": 193315,
                                "text": "Petitioner, Michael Greenlaw was convicted of several drug and firearm felonies, and was sentenced to imprisonment for nearly 37 years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.172,
                                "stop": 44.561,
                                "byte_start": 193315,
                                "byte_stop": 282863,
                                "text": "In calculating his total sentence, the District Court made a mistake overlooking a controlling decision of this Court and despite the Government\u0027s objection, the District Court imposed a 10-year sentence on account that carried a 25-year mandatory minimum term."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.561,
                                "stop": 52.021,
                                "byte_start": 282863,
                                "byte_stop": 312747,
                                "text": "Greenlaw appealed urging among other things that his sentence was too high."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.021,
                                "stop": 58.766,
                                "byte_start": 312747,
                                "byte_stop": 339705,
                                "text": "Anything more than 15 years total, he argued, would be excessive."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.766,
                                "stop": 66.348,
                                "byte_start": 339705,
                                "byte_stop": 370007,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals rejected all of Greenlaw\u0027s arguments but it did not stop there."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.348,
                                "stop": 86.928,
                                "byte_start": 370007,
                                "byte_stop": 452345,
                                "text": "Although, the Government had not asked for a higher sentence by appealing or cross-appealing, the Court of Appeals on its initiative held that Greenlaw\u0027s sentence was too low and ordered the District Court to add 15 years to his prison term."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.928,
                                "stop": 99.25,
                                "byte_start": 452345,
                                "byte_stop": 501664,
                                "text": "We vacate the Court of Appeals\u0027 judgment and hold that because the Government did not appeal or cross-appeal, Greenlaw\u2019s sentence should not have been enlarged."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.25,
                                "stop": 130.531,
                                "byte_start": 501664,
                                "byte_stop": 626739,
                                "text": "In both civil and criminal cases in the first instance, and not appeal, courts in the United States generally followed the principle of party presentation, that means the parties and not the court frame the issues for decision and the courts play a reactive role, they serve as impartial arbiters of matters, the parties present to them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.531,
                                "stop": 142.377,
                                "byte_start": 626739,
                                "byte_stop": 674177,
                                "text": "The cross-appeal rule, pivotal in this case, is both informed by, and illustrative of the party presentation principle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.377,
                                "stop": 154.439,
                                "byte_start": 674177,
                                "byte_stop": 722451,
                                "text": "Under that rule, appellate courts may not reach out to correct the sentencing error when the Government has not invited such error correction by appealing or cross-appealing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.439,
                                "stop": 162.875,
                                "byte_start": 722451,
                                "byte_stop": 756201,
                                "text": "In other words, it takes a cross-appeal to justify a remedy in favor of the appellee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.875,
                                "stop": 173.537,
                                "byte_start": 756201,
                                "byte_stop": 798833,
                                "text": "This Court has called the cross-appeal rule inveterate and certain, and has in no case, ordered an exception to it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.537,
                                "stop": 176.547,
                                "byte_start": 798833,
                                "byte_stop": 810850,
                                "text": "No exception is warranted here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.547,
                                "stop": 198.388,
                                "byte_start": 810850,
                                "byte_stop": 898203,
                                "text": "A provision Congress enacted guides our decision, Congress instructed that the Government may not pursue an appeal of a criminal sentence without the personal approval of the Attorney General, the Solicitor General or the Solicitor General\u0027s designated deputy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.388,
                                "stop": 213.543,
                                "byte_start": 898203,
                                "byte_stop": 958807,
                                "text": "This provision gives the top representatives of the United States in litigation, the prerogative to seek or forgo appellate correction of sentencing errors, however plain they may be."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 213.543,
                                "stop": 224.242,
                                "byte_start": 958807,
                                "byte_stop": 1001648,
                                "text": "We would diminish the force of that instruction while we permit appellate courts to overwrite the assessment of those Justice Department officers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.242,
                                "stop": 241.885,
                                "byte_start": 1001648,
                                "byte_stop": 1072179,
                                "text": "For these reasons and others detailed in our opinion, we conclude that the Court of Appeals erred in ordering Greenlaw\u0027s sentence increased even though the Government did not ask for a higher sentence by pursuing a cross-appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.885,
                                "stop": 246.404,
                                "byte_start": 1072179,
                                "byte_stop": 1090255,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.404,
                                "stop": 258.221,
                                "byte_start": 1090255,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Stevens has joined in full and Justice Breyer has joined in part."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
